main event: Four reddish-orange objects traveling at a high rate of speed were observed by four military observers for three minutes in Tucson, Arizona on April 15, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were irregular in shape and disappeared through a high rate of speed.
The observer believes the objects were aircraft.
The sighting lasted for about 3 minutes.
The objects were observed by four military observers.
The objects were described as traveling at a high rate of speed and disappearing through a high rate of speed.
